,"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e1dc6410-25d7-406a-b015-01c40c9fa16a","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Pushed to Gerrit as change 793 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/793). Extracted the 7 non-retrying update_one apply phases into new leaf dispatch_apply_phases.py (170 LOC); dispatch_one.py 886->748 LOC, graduated off allowlist+ceilings, arch.md remedy row deleted. Deviation: arch.md named _update_one_apply_parent but it uses _call_with_retry (can't move cleanly) — took the non-retrying-phase seam instead. Repointed test_identity_264f_reporter.py monkeypatch to the leaf. Local gates green: make lint clean, test_module_size_contract (5 passed), tests/unit/rebar_reconciler all passed. Awaiting Gerrit LLM-Review + Verified before close.","timestamp":1784398463367559001}],"created_at":1784397260902067001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"Graduate `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_one.py` off the module-size\nallowlist (currently ~886 LOC, soft cap 800) by extracting a cohesive cluster of the\nNON-retrying `update_one` apply phases into a new leaf sibling\n`src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_apply_phases.py`.\n\n## Seam\n\n`update_one` is a thin sequencer over per-phase helpers. The phases split cleanly into\ntwo groups: those that funnel Jira writes through the shared `_call_with_retry` backoff\nhub, and those that do NOT. The retrying phases (`_update_one_apply_parent`,\n`_update_one_scalar_update`, `_update_one_dispatch_labels`, `_update_one_dispatch_links`)\nSTAY in `dispatch_one` alongside `_call_with_retry` itself. The NON-retrying phases MOVE\nto the new leaf: `_OUTBOUND_BATCH_ALLOWLIST`, `_jira_account_id_for`, `_load_alert_store`,\n`_record_reporter_alert`, `_update_one_apply_reporter`, `_update_one_filter_fields`,\n`_update_one_dispatch_comments` (~132 LOC). None of these touch `_call_with_retry`, so the\nnew module is a true LEAF (it imports nothing from `dispatch_one`; its only cross-module\nuses are lazy in-function imports of `rebar`, `rebar._commands.identity`, and\n`rebar_reconciler._loader`). `dispatch_one` re-imports the 3 phase functions\n(`_update_one_apply_reporter`, `_update_one_filter_fields`, `_update_one_dispatch_comments`)\nso `update_one`'s bare-name calls and `dispatch_one.<phase>` attribute access keep resolving.\n\n## Deviation from the architecture.md remedy row\n\nThe current `docs/architecture.md` offenders row for this file names its next seam as\nextracting `_update_one_apply_parent` (plus the assignee sentinel pop) into\n`dispatch_apply_phases.py`. That named symbol CANNOT move cleanly: `_update_one_apply_parent`\ncalls the shared `_call_with_retry` hub (`_call_with_retry(client.set_parent, ...)`), so\nmoving it would force the leaf to import `_call_with_retry` back from `dispatch_one` and\ncreate a bidirectional dependency. This ticket therefore takes a different, code-accurate\nseam — the \"non-retrying apply phases\" grouping above — which keeps the new file a strict\nleaf. The arch.md row is superseded; this ticket DELETES that remedy row (the file graduates\noff the gate entirely). This ticket does NOT claim arch.md already records this exact seam.\n\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor: no signature or logic changes, symbols are moved verbatim\nand re-exported. E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing test suite is the oracle.\nThe one required test edit repoints `test_identity_264f_reporter.py`'s\n`monkeypatch.setattr(dispatch, \"_record_reporter_alert\", ...)` to the leaf module (the symbol\nmoves there), while the direct `dispatch._update_one_apply_reporter(...)` calls keep working\nvia the re-export.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_apply_phases.py` exists, 100-800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_apply_phases.py`)\n- [ ] `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_one.py` <= 800 LOC (verify: `wc -l src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_one.py`)\n- [ ] `dispatch_one.py` absent from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` and `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt`; its `docs/architecture.md` offenders remedy row deleted (verify: `grep -c dispatch_one .github/module-size-allowlist.txt .github/module-size-ceilings.txt docs/architecture.md` all 0)\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q` passes\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/unit/rebar_reconciler -q` is green (no behavior change)\n- [ ] back-compat: `dispatch_one._update_one_apply_reporter`, `dispatch_one._update_one_filter_fields`, `dispatch_one._update_one_dispatch_comments` still resolve (re-exported)\n- [ ] `make lint` and `make typecheck` clean","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_apply_phases.py","reason":"new leaf module holding the moved non-retrying update_one apply phases"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/dispatch_one.py","reason":"remove moved symbols; re-import the 3 phase functions for back-compat"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_identity_264f_reporter.py","reason":"repoint monkeypatch of _record_reporter_alert to the leaf module"},{"path":".github/module-size-allowlist.txt","reason":"remove dispatch_one.py row (graduates off gate)"},{"path":".github/module-size-ceilings.txt","reason":"remove dispatch_one.py ceiling row"},{"path":"docs/architecture.md","reason":"delete the superseded dispatch_one.py offenders remedy row"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","716f-b917-9fc8-41f5"]],"parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","parent_status_uuid":"0715e6e3-1d33-4b86-9e2f-6939002ffea7","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":1,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["module-size"],"ticket_id":"744a-d299-970b-4140","ticket_type":"story","title":"Graduate dispatch_one.py off module-size gate: extract non-retrying update_one apply phases into dispatch_apply_phases.py leaf","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["18b623ec-ed6e-4f52-8b91-6d81618df09e","66330783-00aa-47ee-a657-f7700a72e098","776eeb7c-c555-4a35-9525-3a78461d8736","0715e6e3-1d33-4b86-9e2f-6939002ffea7","4fa71f59-907b-466f-b4eb-7f6ace752f28","f993f03b-724c-4a4e-963a-5a8101892514","57bbba69-8563-4a34-b911-570f1edd6965"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784399940927445524,"uuid":"4fe2c73b-edd0-4ace-9db1-366e986b813b"}